Class Processors

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.oracle.coherence.grpc.proxy.Processors
  • public final class Processors
extends Object
    A utility class of InvocableMap.EntryProcessor classes used by the NamedCacheService.
    Since:
    14.1.2
    Author:
    Mahesh Kannan 2019.11.01, Jonathan Knight 2019.11.07

      A base InvocableMap.EntryProcessor.
      static class  Processors.ContainsValueProcessor
      An InvocableMap.EntryProcessor that checks if the mapping for the key exists in the cache.
      static class  Processors.GetProcessor
      An InvocableMap.EntryProcessor that obtains the Binary value mapped to a given key in a cache.
      static class  Processors.ProcessorWithValue<T>
      An InvocableMap.EntryProcessor that contains a value.
      static class  Processors.PutAllProcessor
      An InvocableMap.EntryProcessor that updates the mapping of a number of key to values in a cache.
      static class  Processors.PutIfAbsentProcessor
      An InvocableMap.EntryProcessor that puts the specified value in the cache only if there is no existing mapping for the key.
      static class  Processors.PutProcessor
      An InvocableMap.EntryProcessor that updates the mapping of a key to a value in a cache.
      static class  Processors.RemoveBlindProcessor
      An InvocableMap.EntryProcessor that removes a cache entry without de-serializing keys or values and returns no result.
      static class  Processors.RemoveProcessor
      An InvocableMap.EntryProcessor that obtains the Binary value mapped to a given key in a cache.
      static class  Processors.ReplaceMappingProcessor
      An InvocableMap.EntryProcessor that replaces a specific existing mapping in a cache.
      static class  Processors.ReplaceProcessor
      An InvocableMap.EntryProcessor that replaces an existing mapping in a cache.
